    <div class="article-intro"><div class="article-hero"><img src="/assets/screens/en-point-720.webp" width="1280" height="720" alt="VeVolt screen with charging-station connector details" fetchpriority="high"></div><header class="article-header"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="signal"></span>VeVolt guide</p><h1>Electric-car connectors: Type 2, CCS2, CHAdeMO and GB/T</h1><p class="lede">A charger can be close and powerful but still be unusable if its connector does not match the vehicle. Compatibility should be checked before the route begins.</p><p class="article-meta">Updated 18/07/2026 · 9 min read</p></header></div>
    <div class="article-layout"><div class="article-body"><section><h2>Separate AC from DC charging</h2><p>Type 2 is widely associated with AC charging, while CCS2 combines AC pins with additional DC contacts. CHAdeMO and GB/T serve different vehicle and market ecosystems.</p></section><section><h2>Match the connector to the vehicle</h2><p>Use the vehicle manual and charging-port label as the source of truth. Adapters are not universal and should only be used when approved for the vehicle and charger.</p><ul><li>Connector standard</li><li>AC or DC</li><li>Vehicle power limit</li><li>Cable attached or required</li><li>Approved adapter requirements</li></ul></section><section><h2>Check more than the plug shape</h2><p>Connector compatibility does not guarantee maximum speed. The car&#39;s onboard charger, DC limit and the station&#39;s available power still determine performance.</p></section><section><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><div class="faq-list"><details class="faq-item"><summary>Is Type 2 the same as CCS2?</summary><p>CCS2 includes the Type 2 section but adds DC contacts for fast charging.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Can an adapter make every charger compatible?</summary><p>No. Electrical standards, communication and manufacturer approval still matter.</p></details></div></section></div>
    <aside class="article-aside"><h2>Use VeVolt in your routine</h2><p>Find chargers, check reports, plan alternatives and record your experience in one app.</p><a class="button primary" href="/en/testers">Join the test</a><h2>Sources and further reading</h2><ul class="source-list"><li><a href="https://www.gov.br/inmetro/pt-br/assuntos/regulamentacao/analise-de-impacto-regulatorio/realizadas/2024/conectores-para-carregamento-de-veiculos-eletricos-plug-in/relatorio" rel="noopener noreferrer">Inmetro - Analysis of electric-vehicle charging connectors</a></li><li><a href="https://afdc.energy.gov/fuels/electricity-stations" rel="noopener noreferrer">U.S. Department of Energy - Electric Vehicle Charging Stations</a></li></ul></aside></div>
